paragraphs.text: You should always floss even when you’re really, really tired.
paragraphs.name: 2c3e

paragraphs.text: Also, as of this week, I’m gonna start posting every OTHER Wednesday. At least for the next few weeks.
paragraphs.name: 8fb6

paragraphs.text: Now, I assure you I have very valid reasons for changing my blogging schedule and it’s not because I’m lazy. If I was lazy, I wouldn’t even write this, derrr.

(A) I’ve become super busy and, more than anything, I do not want the quality of my posts to suffer. Of course, I realize I’ve set a very low bar and “quality” is a subjective term, especially when I use it, but it could actually get worse. I know, right?! How is that even possible? Just friggin’ trust me (for instance, I could start using the word “friggin’”).
paragraphs.name: c215

paragraphs.text: (B) I’m working on my very own… wait for it… ThunderPuff website! Unfortunately, it’s taking longer than I anticipated due to my inability to code.

paragraphs.text: I keep a bag of those little handy flossers in my car, in the kitchen, in the bathroom, at work in my desk, in my purse. I hate the feeling of having anything stuck between my teeth so I floss constantly after every meal/snack. That’s not to say I did this growing up, but as a dental-bill paying adult, hell yeah.
